
                                                        +-------+
                                                        |  .DH  |
                                                        +-------+

DEFINE HEADING defines the "text" and "table of contents" format-
ting conditions for the Heading Level control words.

     +-------+---------------------------------------------+
     |       |                                             |
     |       |    <SET m> n <<SKBF n> <SPAF n>             |
     |       |               <SPAFC n>                     |
     |       |               <TCIN n> <TCOF n>             |
     |  .DH  |               <BR|NBR> <CE|NCE>             |
     |       |               <OJ|NOJ> <PA|NPA>             |
     |       |               <TC|NTC> <TO|NTO>             |
     |       |               <TS|NTS> <UP|NUP>             |
     |       |               <US|NUS>>                     |
     |       |                                             |
     +-------+---------------------------------------------+

<.B+><SET m>:   <.B->specifies to  which of  the  ten (0  to 9)   table-of-<.NORMAL>
   contents workareas this definition  applies.   If omitted,  it
   applies to the  one currently being used (0,  at  the start of
   SCRIPT processing).
<.B+>n <options>:   <.B->specifies to which  of the  ten (0 to  9)  heading<.NORMAL>
   levels this definition  applies.   See the Head  Level control
   word (.HL) for the initial setting of the options.
<.B+>SKBF n:   <.B->the number  of skips  (.SK)  to  be printed  before the<.NORMAL>
   heading in the text.
<.B+>SPAF<C> n:  <.B->the number of spaces  or conditional spaces (.SP)  to<.NORMAL>
   be printed after the heading in the text.
<.B+>TCIN  n:  <.B->the  indent  value  for the  heading  in  the table  of<.NORMAL>
   contents.
<.B+>TCOF  n:  <.B->the  offset  value  for the  heading  in  the table  of<.NORMAL>
   contents.
<.B+><N>BR:  <.B->specifies whether  to cause a break after  the heading in<.NORMAL>
   the text.
<.B+><N>CE:  <.B->specifies whether to center the heading in the text.<.NORMAL>
<.B+><N>OJ:  <.B->specifies whether to out-justify the heading in the text.<.NORMAL>
   OJ and CE  are mutually exclusive.   If both  are specified CE
   takes precedence.
<.B+><N>PA:  <.B->specifies whether  to do a .PA before the  heading in the<.NORMAL>
   text.
<.B+><N>TC:  <.B->specifies whether to include the  heading in the table of<.NORMAL>
   contents.
<.B+><N>TO:  <.B->specifies  whether to  include this  heading ONLY  in the<.NORMAL>
   table of contents.   If TO is specified,  the heading will not
   be printed in the text.
<.B+><N>TS:  <.B->specifies whether to "type a  space" after the heading in<.NORMAL>
   the table of contents.
<.B+><N>UP:  <.B->specifies whether to convert  the heading to uppercase in<.NORMAL>
   the text.   (Headings included in the table of contents always
   appear "as entered".)

<.B+><N>US:  <.B->specifies whether to underscore the heading in the text.<.NORMAL>

This control word does not cause a break.   See the example given
with the .TC control word.

